cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper discusses the Byzantine attack and defense strategies in cognitive radio networks, which involves signal detection techniques, hypothesis testing, and data fusion. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper also covers topics related to information theory (cs.IT), system and control theory (cs.SY), and multimedia (cs.MM) as they relate to the defense mechanisms against the Byzantine attack. Finally, the paper also falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it discusses secure CSS and robust defense schemes.
